DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Imaging data acquired over a single time frame. The result is a single frame that represents the average amount of radioactivity during the scan period. RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: Time is the continuum of experience in which events pass from the future through the present to the past.  It may also refer to a specific point in this continuum or to the interval separating two points.  It is generally measured in minutes, days, months, or years.
